					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13195319#post-4580458</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13195319/scp-5296#post-4580458</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 03 Apr 2020 21:04:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DarkStuff</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1581620</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>You're probably looking for a more in-depth comment than this, but, yeap! This is a better version. It's been a while since I read the original but this is an upvote from me. There are some grammar errors (some floating &quot;the&quot;s and &quot;<em>excluding the lack of a briefing</em>&quot; should just be <em>excluding the briefing</em>), but overall it reads pretty well. I do have to wonder if the Foundation really <em>would</em> care this much about ethics &#8212; &quot;giving it some basic rights&quot; as that one guy said &#8212; when they lock people up for the rest of their lives. I mean, the Ethics Committee guards against unnecessary torture, both mental and physical, but their mission statement is to contain things. Not so pretty. Anyways, upvote from me, good job!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
